## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="c3d26-102">O formato de semântica de padrão de System. Speech está de acordo com o W3C [interpretação de semântica para reconhecimento de fala (SISR) versão 1.0](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=201765), em que o formato para `tag` elementos que contêm o script é `semantics/1.0`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c3d26-102">The default semantic format for System.Speech conforms to the W3C [Semantic Interpretation for Speech Recognition (SISR) Version 1.0](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=201765), where the format for `tag` elements that contain script is `semantics/1.0`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c3d26-103">Você deve especificar o script para <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag> objetos usando esse formato.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c3d26-103">You must specify the script for <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag> objects using this format.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c3d26-104">Na sintaxe de `semantics/1.0`:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c3d26-104">In the syntax of `semantics/1.0`:</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="c3d26-105">A variável de regra do elemento de regra contido é identificado por "out".</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c3d26-105">The Rule Variable of the containing rule element is identified by "out".</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="c3d26-106">O nome do objeto que tem acesso à variável de regra de elementos de regra fora do elemento recipiente de regra é identificado por "regras".</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c3d26-106">The name of the object that has access to the Rule Variable of rule elements outside the containing rule element is identified by "rules".</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="c3d26-107">O resultado da última referenciado regra que corresponde à declaração pode ser representado por "rules.latest()".</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c3d26-107">The result from the latest referenced rule that matches the utterance can be represented by "rules.latest()".</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="c3d26-108">Você também pode associar um valor semântico com uma frase em uma gramática sem usar script, usando o <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsNameValueTag> objeto.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c3d26-108">You can also associate a semantic value with a phrase in a grammar without using script, using the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsNameValueTag> object.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="c3d26-109">O exemplo a seguir cria uma gramática para escolher as cidades de um voo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c3d26-109">The following example creates a grammar for choosing the cities for a flight.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c3d26-110">O exemplo usa <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag> para atribuir um valor semântico para cada cidade, o que é o código de aeroporto da cidade.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c3d26-110">The example uses <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag> to assign a semantic value to each city, which is the code for the city's airport.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c3d26-111">O exemplo também usa <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag> para atribuir uma chave semântica separada para cada uma das duas referências feitas pelo <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRuleRef> objeto denominado `cityRef` para o <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> objeto chamado `cities`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c3d26-111">The example also uses <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag> to assign a separate semantic key for each of the two references made by the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRuleRef> object named `cityRef` to the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> object named `cities`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c3d26-112">As chaves de semânticas identificam uma cidade identificada como a cidade de partida ou a cidade de chegada de voo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c3d26-112">The semantic keys identify a recognized city as the departure city or the arrival city for the flight.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c3d26-113">O manipulador para o <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.SpeechRecognized> evento usa as chaves para recuperar a semântica de resultado do reconhecimento.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c3d26-113">The handler for the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.SpeechRecognized> event uses the keys to retrieve the semantics from the recognition result.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="c3d26-114">No exemplo de código, "out" refere-se a variável de regra de que o contém <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c3d26-114">In the code example, "out" refers to the Rule Variable of the containing <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c3d26-115">A expressão "out. LeavingFrom"refere-se a propriedade chamada `LeavingFrom` de variável de regra na regra denominada `bookFlight`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c3d26-115">The expression "out.LeavingFrom" refers to the property named `LeavingFrom` of the Rule Variable on the rule named `bookFlight`.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="c3d26-116">A expressão "rules.flightCities" refere-se a variável de regra na regra cuja <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Id%2A> é `flightCities`, e qual é o destino de uma referência de regra.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c3d26-116">The expression "rules.flightCities" refers to the Rule Variable on the rule whose <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Id%2A> is `flightCities`, and which is the target of a rule reference.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c3d26-117">No exemplo, a expressão "out. LeavingFrom=rules.flightCities;"atribui o valor da regra de cujos <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Id%2A> está `flightCities` à propriedade chamada `LeavingFrom` de variável de regra na regra denominada `bookFlight`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c3d26-117">In the example, the expression "out.LeavingFrom=rules.flightCities;" assigns the value from the rule whose <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Id%2A> is `flightCities` to the property named `LeavingFrom` of the Rule Variable on the rule named `bookFlight`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c3d26-118">Ver [semântica resultados conteúdo](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/622291af-615c-4a15-9014-2933aa3f89fe), [referência de nome de regra de gramática](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/0777e975-8665-4cc3-957b-752743cb1bb9), e [referenciando de referência de regra de gramática](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/dec3a809-9aa2-4139-893f-3a549ca1e03e) para obter mais informações.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c3d26-118">See [Semantic Results Content](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/622291af-615c-4a15-9014-2933aa3f89fe), [Grammar Rule Name Referencing](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/0777e975-8665-4cc3-957b-752743cb1bb9), and [Grammar Rule Reference Referencing](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/dec3a809-9aa2-4139-893f-3a549ca1e03e) for more information.</span></span>  
  
```  
using System;  
using System.Speech.Recognition;  
using System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar;  
  
namespace SampleRecognition  
{  
  class Program  
  {  
    static void Main(string[] args)  
  
    // Initialize a SpeechRecognitionEngine object.  
    {  
      using (SpeechRecognitionEngine recognizer =  
         new SpeechRecognitionEngine(new System.Globalization.CultureInfo("en-US")))  
      {  
  
        // Create a rule for the cities, assign a semantic value to each city.  
        SrgsRule cities = new SrgsRule("flightCities");  
        SrgsItem chi = new SrgsItem("Chicago");  
        chi.Add(new SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag("out = \"ORD\";"));  
        SrgsItem bos = new SrgsItem("Boston");  
        bos.Add(new SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag("out = \"BOS\";"));  
        SrgsItem mia = new SrgsItem("Miami");  
        mia.Add(new SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag("out = \"MIA\";"));  
        SrgsItem dal = new SrgsItem("Dallas");  
        dal.Add(new SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag("out = \"DFW\";"));  
  
        SrgsOneOf airports = new SrgsOneOf(chi, bos, mia, dal);  
        cities.Add(airports);  
        cities.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Private;  
  
        // Create a rule reference to the rule for cities.  
        SrgsRuleRef cityRef = new SrgsRuleRef(cities);  
  
        // Create the root rule for the grammar.  
        SrgsRule bookFlight = new SrgsRule("flightBooker");  
        bookFlight.Add(new SrgsItem("I want to fly from"));  
        bookFlight.Add(cityRef);  
        bookFlight.Add(new SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag("out.LeavingFrom=rules.flightCities;"));  
        bookFlight.Add(new SrgsItem("to"));  
        bookFlight.Add(cityRef);  
        bookFlight.Add(new SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag("out.GoingTo=rules.flightCities;"));  
        bookFlight.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Public;  
  
        // Initialize the SrgsDocument, set the root rule, add rules to the collection.  
        SrgsDocument itinerary = new SrgsDocument(bookFlight);  
        itinerary.Rules.Add(cities);  
  
        // Create a Grammar object and load it to the recognizer.  
        Grammar g = new Grammar(itinerary);  
        g.Name = ("City Chooser");  
        recognizer.LoadGrammarAsync(g);  
  
        // Configure recognizer input.                  
        recognizer.SetInputToDefaultAudioDevice();  
  
        // Attach a handler for the SpeechRecognized event.  
        recognizer.SpeechRecognized +=  
          new EventHandler<SpeechRecognizedEventArgs>(recognizer_SpeechRecognized);  
  
        // Start recognition.  
        recognizer.RecognizeAsync();  
        Console.WriteLine("Starting asynchronous recognition...");  
  
        // Keep the console window open.  
        Console.ReadLine();  
      }  
    }  
  
    // Write to the console the text and the semantics from the recognition result.  
    static void recognizer_SpeechRecognized(object sender, SpeechRecognizedEventArgs e)  
    {  
      Console.WriteLine("Speech recognized: " + e.Result.Text);  
      Console.WriteLine();  
      Console.WriteLine("Semantic results:");  
      Console.WriteLine("  The departure city is: " + e.Result.Semantics["LeavingFrom"].Value);  
      Console.WriteLine("  The arrival city is: " + e.Result.Semantics["GoingTo"].Value);  
    }  
  }  
}  
  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="c3d26-119">O seguinte é a forma XML da gramática gerada pelo código no exemplo acima.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c3d26-119">The following is the XML form of the grammar generated by the code in the example above.</span></span>  
  
```xml  
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>  
<grammar xml:lang="en-US" root="flightBooker" tag-format="semantics/1.0"   
version="1.0" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2001/06/grammar">  
  
  <rule id="flightBooker" scope="public">  
    <item> I want to fly from </item>  
    <ruleref uri="#flightCities" />   
    <tag> out.LeavingFrom=rules.flightCities; </tag>  
    <item> to </item>  
    <ruleref uri="#flightCities" />   
    <tag> out.GoingTo=rules.flightCities; </tag>  
  </rule>  
  
  <rule id="flightCities" scope="private">  
    <one-of>  
      <item> Chicago <tag> out="ORD"; </tag></item>  
      <item> Boston <tag> out="BOS"; </tag></item>  
      <item> Miami <tag> out="MIA"; </tag></item>  
      <item> Dallas <tag> out="DFW"; </tag></item>  
    </one-of>  
  </rule>  
  
</grammar>  
```
